President Hassan Rohani ready to
decommission  Iran â€™s Fordo uranium enrichment facility, near the
city of Qom, in exchange for an easing of international
sanctions, Der Spiegel says.
*Magazine cites unidentified intelligence officials on
decommissioning.
*Rohani will close down Fordo, which started operations in late
2011, and allow international inspectors to monitor removal of
centrifuges, according to German publication.
*Rohani may demand U.S. and EU rescind sanctions against Iran,
lift ban on oil exports and allow central bank to conduct
business overseas: Spiegel.
*Rohani is scheduled to address the United Nations General
